						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Sik wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">A better example [of Select as pause] would be After Burner (which has Start mapped to the afterburner =P)</div><br />How else should a game map buttons to three actions without having to be ported to the Genesis?<br /><ul><li>Jump, primary tool, secondary tool </li><li>Jump, attack, guard </li><li>Jump, attack, dash (Mega Man X) </li><li>Jump, pass, run (NBA Jam) </li><li>Primary attack, secondary attack, guard (Mortal Kombat; Smash Bros.) </li><li>Primary tool, pick up, run (Animal Crossing) although you could do like City Folk and not allow running if there is something under your feet to pick up </li></ul>No, up can't always be jump if it's already bound to climb ladder, aim upward, or walk north.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">3gengames wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">if you can't avoid an attack with moderate skill, the design of said enemy is wrong. </div><br />Is Sephiroth's design wrong in Final Fantasy VII? <a href="http://xkcd.com/299/" class="postlink">[Spoiler]</a> can't avoid being killed off for real just before the halfway point.</div>

